  'story.title': 'From Sevares to the World: Why build a <strong>digital hórreo</strong>?',
  'story.intro': 'I am <strong>Jorge Luis Álvarez Solís (Jlasolis)</strong>. Son of Jorge and Pili, grandson of Ángel, Marina, Zulema, and Marcelino. I was born and raised in <strong>Sevares</strong>, where I learned that things that last are built on solid foundations and through community.',
  'story.edu': 'Many of you might wonder what a programmer—trained at <strong>Seresco</strong> and in the cafeteria of the Faculty of Computer Science—is doing in this web privacy "mess." Life has led me through many trades, always with an entrepreneurial spirit, but Open Source has always been a special part, a <strong><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stone_Soup" target="_blank">"stone soup"</a></strong>: that recipe where everyone contributes what they have so that, in the end, we all eat.',
  'story.esbillar.title': 'What is "Esbillar" the web?',
  'story.esbillar.body': 'For those not familiar with the term, a <strong>CMP (Consent Management Platform)</strong> is the tool that manages cookies. But I prefer to explain it as we do in Asturias: <strong>when you "esbillar," you separate the ear of corn from the leaves.</strong> A CMP does the same with your browsing data: it separates the cookies necessary for the web to function from those used for statistics or marketing, leaving only those you truly accept.',
  'story.moment.title': 'The moment is now (and AI is to blame)',
  'story.moment.body': 'It is <strong>2026</strong>. Current CMP pricing models are, frankly, a robbery. They charge exorbitant amounts for a solution that, technically, is not an insurmountable challenge. With the power and ease that <strong>AI</strong> gives us today, there is no excuse: it is the perfect time for a reasonable alternative. We started with many resources made by AI but with the intention that, as a community, we humanize this common project.',
  'story.open.title': 'Why Open Source and Self-Managed?',
  'story.open.andecha': '<strong>Andecha and Sestaferia:</strong> Having <strong>Esbilla CMP</strong> be open source means people can help improve it collectively. It\'s the spirit of <strong>sestaferia</strong> or working in <strong>andecha</strong>: if we fix the road together, we all travel better.',
  'story.open.horreo': '<strong>Your Granary, Your Rules:</strong> Data sovereignty means that instead of storing in a multinational\'s giant warehouse, you store and manage your information on your own machine. Like that <strong>hórreo</strong> that protects the grain from moisture and pests, Esbilla lets you set up the system in <strong>Docker</strong> to isolate your data from unwanted trackers. We also use the classic Open Source formula "Give away the recipe, open a restaurant" by offering SaaS services so anyone without technical knowledge can use our Cookie manager or by offering our services to set up the system on your infrastructure.',
